On Sat, 24 Nov 2001, Bhanu Prakash,ilabs ltd wrote:

&gt; hi friends
&gt; just i have a small things to ask
&gt; 1) how to test private methods

One thing I&#39;ve found successfull is to make an inner class my test object,
like:

public class Foo { // The class I&#39;m going to test
    private int doit() { ... } // The function I&#39;m going to test

    private class MyTestClass extends junit.framework.TestCase {
        public void testDoit() {
            assertTrue(doit() == 3); // Make sure doit works correctly
        }
    }

    public static junit.framework.Test suite() {
        junit.framework.Test retval = new junit.framework.Test();
        retval.addTest(new MyTestClass(&quot;testDoit&quot;));
    }
}

The inner class (MyTestClass) can now see the private doit() function to
test it.

&gt; 2) how to catch test result and store in the file. please if any body
&gt; have the program please send me as attachment.

Short answer: redirect stdout and stderr into a file.

I&#39;m using bash and make on a unix box.  I just do:
$ make run 2&gt;&1 | tee make.res

Of course, I&#39;m using the text interface, not the fancy GUI interface.  One
of the advantages of doing so...

